## Verification you can run

To confirm on a running system or SITL:

1. Inspect parameter: `param show SENS_IMU_MODE` — 1 means VotedSensorsUpdate is the active voter feeding the (single) EKF2; 0 means EKF2Selector is the arbiter.
2. Check uORB publishers at runtime: `uorb top vehicle_attitude` and `uorb top sensor_combined`. In `SENS_IMU_MODE=0` mode, `estimator_selector_status` will tick; in `SENS_IMU_MODE=1` it will not be published.
3. Read `src/modules/ekf2/EKF2.cpp:2651-2663` to see the construction gate for `EKF2Selector`, and `:453-469` to see the `sensor_combined` vs `vehicle_imu` subscription split.

